# G1 Teleoperation via MediaPipe Pose

This project enables real-time teleoperation of the Unitree G1 robot's arm using human upper-body movement captured by a webcam and processed with MediaPipe Pose.

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
g1_teleop/
├── main.py                         # Entry point (run MediaPipe + control loop)
├── config/
│   └── joint_limits.yaml           # G1 joint range, safety configs
├── controllers/
│   ├── sdk_controller.py           # Sends joint angles via Unitree Python SDK
│   └── ros2_controller.py          # (Optional) ROS 2 control module
├── tracking/
│   └── pose_tracker.py             # MediaPipe Pose + joint angle extraction
├── utils/
│   ├── joint_mapping.py            # Maps human angles → G1 joint angles
├── simulation/
│   └── sim_overlay.py              # Visualizes simulated G1 movements
├── README.md                       # Project instructions & setup
└── requirements.txt                # Python dependencies
```

---

## ✅ Setup

### 1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone <your-repo-url> && cd g1_teleop
```

### 2. Create a virtual environment (optional)
```bash
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
```

### 3. Install dependencies
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## 🎥 Run the Visual Simulator

```bash
python -m simulation.sim_overlay
```

---

## 🤖 Run Full Teleoperation

Make sure your Unitree G1 is:
- Powered on and in PC control mode
- Accessible at the IP address defined in `main.py`

Then run:
```bash
python main.py
```

---

## ⚙️ Configuration

- Edit `config/joint_limits.yaml` to adjust allowed motion range per joint.
- Customize the control logic in `utils/joint_mapping.py` if needed.

---

## 📦 Requirements

See `requirements.txt` for full dependency list.